  yield summary вүЎ "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language where programs are documents and execution fills in values. Cells start as natural language (soft) and crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure.

Core syntax uses вҠў for cell declaration, вҲҙ for soft bodies, вҠў= for hard bodies, вҠЁ for oracle assertions, В§ for quotation, В«В» for interpolation, вүЎ for binding, and вҶ’ for output access.

Execution follows Kahn's algorithm (eval-one): find ready cells, evaluate one, spawn oracle claim cells, freeze if claims pass. Key properties: document-is-state, monotonicity, non-termination by design, confluence, content addressing, fusion of classical and semantic substrates.

В§ enables code-as-data and reflection. Crystallization moves cells from soft to hard вҖ” verification crystallizes before computation. Oracles are claim cells spawned by cell-zero; retry is graph rewrite preserving immutability.

вҠўвҲҳ provides evolution loops with interface freeze constraint. Self-crystallization: вҲҙ is the specification, вҠў= is the proven optimization. Bootstrap trajectory: soft everywhere вҶ’ hard core, soft frontier.

вҠўвҠў spawners grow the frontier (semantic automata, never-terminating). Proof-carrying computation: LLM finds solutions (NP), crystallized verifiers check them (P)."

